g.text: - field GroupsFound: Number of groups found
- field candidatesToRemove: The number of sentences minus the number of groups
(i.e. the number of sentences that could potentially be removed as unique ones from
the original document), as a number.
SessionData
- field members: TextDuplicates grouped by similarity
- field threshold: similarity threshold used at creation
- field standardMeasure: which TextDuplicates was acting as the standard measure
at creation.
- field variance: Some variance or IQR metric for the similarity scores' distribution
- average score for the similarity scores
TextDuplicatesGroup
- stores Text objects with the same text content
- stores embedded vector for that text content
- stores its similarity score coupled with the
associated textDuplicateGroup id, in a hashmap.
- Stores if it were the standardMeasure for some
GroupId.
TextDuplicates
- Stores text content
- Stores attributes (semid)
- Stores XPath position in XML
